            The area bounded by the graph of <m> y = \frac{1}{x}</m>,
            the <m>x</m>-axis,
            and the vertical line <m>x = 1</m> is infinite or unbounded.
            However, The area bounded by the graph of <m> y = \frac{1}{x^{3/2}}</m>,
            the <m>x</m>-axis, and the vertical line <m>x = 1</m> is equal to 2.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </solution>
